    section.description
      h3.hidden Description
      .content
        .subsection
          p Csstetic is a set of code snippets which joined together solve common <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User_interface">ui design</a> tasks. It does not "reset" or overwrite project's styling, that makes it easy to use with any existing framework or as a standalone tool. For rapid prototyping <strong>Classic</strong> <i><small>(compiled css)</small></i> version should be enough, while <strong>Semantic</strong> <i><small>(scss mixins)</small></i> require any sass compiler and results in clean <i><small>(semantic)</small></i> html code.



    section.comparison
      .content
        h3 Comparison
        .difference-paragraph
          p <strong>Classic</strong> version uses simmilar syntax to other common css frameworks:

          code.
            &lt;span class=&quot;fw-button fw-size-md fw-bg-red&quot;&gt;button&lt;/span&gt;

          p <strong>Semantic</strong> version moves all the styling back to scss file:
          pre
            code.
              Html:
              &lt;span&gt;button&lt;/span&gt;

              Scss:
              span {
                @include fw-button;
                @include fw-size-base;
                @include fw-size(md);
                background: fw-color(red);
              }
        .comparison-table
          .row
            .col
            .col
              p Classic
            .col
              p Semantic
            .col
              p Description
          .row
            .col
              p Price
            .col
              p Free
            .col
              p Free
            .col
              p Classic version is one variant of compiled Csstetic, all the goodies available through mixins and functions come with Semantic version.
          .row
            .col
              p File size
            .col
              p 50kB
            .col
              p 0+ kB
            .col
              p 50kb is the file size for csstetic.css file containing ready to use copy & paste components. Semantic version (0+ kB _csstetic.scss) adds only this code, which has been truly used in your project.
          .row
            .col
              p Selectors
            .col
              p predefined
            .col
              p custom
            .col
              p Classic is better for rapid development, because of precompiled class="fw-..." selectors, while Semantic allows you to create custom selectors like class="music-player", then compiling it.
          .row
            .col
              p Difficulty
            .col
              p easy
            .col
              p medium
            .col
              p In fact, both versions come with ready to copy & paste cody snippets, but since Semantic version requires using .scss files instead of .css, it has been marked as medium.
          .row
            .col
              p Responsiveness
            .col
              p partially
            .col
              p fully
            .col
              p Classic version is prepared for most common use cases for each device size but advanced features such as fw-scale(...); or fw-media(tablet){...}; wouldn't be possible without goodness of scss language.
          .row
            .col
              p Customizable
            .col
              p medium
            .col
              p high
            .col
              p While building layout with class="feature-1 feature-2" is quick and easy, sometimes you may need to customize the feature through options available in .scss mixins and by adding custom css properties.
          .row
            .col
              p Semantic html
            .col
              p no
            .col
              p yes
            .col
              p That's where "Semantic" name comes from - all features can be packed in one html class="my-button" or even target entire &lt;button&gt; tag without touching the html file, leaving the code as clear as possible.
          .row
